      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>* Mariano Favetto, creative director at Lautrec Nazca Saatchi &amp; Saatchi, Buenos Aires, part of Saatchi &amp; Saatchi P.L.C., was named chief creative officer of a sibling agency, Conill Advertising, New York, succeeding Luz de Armas, who left.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>* Mariano Favetto, creative director at Lautrec Nazca Saatchi &amp; Saatchi, Buenos Aires, part of Saatchi &amp; Saatchi P.L.C., was named chief creative officer of a sibling agency, Conill Advertising, New York, succeeding Luz de Armas, who left.</p>
        <p>* Greg Johnston was named to the new position of vice president and creative director at McCann-Erickson Washington, part of the McCann-Erickson World Group unit of the Interpublic Group of Cos. He had been senior vice president and associate creative director at Arnold Advertising, McLean, Va., part of Arnold Communications.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
